  "response_text": "The commercial opens in a dim, teal-lit hospital room that appears to be a neonatal intensive care setting. A clear incubator sits in the center, surrounded by medical monitors, tubing, shelves, and clinical equipment. A female-presenting healthcare worker in blue scrubs stands beside the incubator, leaning forward with her hands near the baby inside, her posture careful and attentive. The view then moves close to a tiny newborn’s hand, softly lit and curled near the baby’s body, emphasizing how small and delicate the infant is. The healthcare worker’s face appears in close-up as she looks downward with a gentle, focused expression.\n\nA very small newborn lies on a white cushion inside the incubator, wearing a tiny white diaper. The baby’s eyes are closed, and a thin clear tube rests near the nose, suggesting medical support. One little hand is covered with a red knitted mitten shaped like a boxing glove, with a small white patch marked with an “H,” visually making the infant look like a tiny fighter. The transparent oval openings of the incubator frame the baby in the foreground. Small white on-screen text along the bottom reads, “Baby is AI-created for safety of baby in NICU.”\n\nA blue-gloved hand reaches into a white storage shelf stocked with red Huggies boxes. The boxes show the large white “HUGGIES” brand name, and some packaging appears to be for Little Snugglers. The gloved hand pulls out a small folded diaper or diaper insert from the shelf. In a close-up, blue-gloved hands hold and adjust a tiny Huggies diaper, with the green “HUGGIES” logo and small cloud graphics visible on the front. The diaper is then shown being positioned on the baby, fitting beneath a soft white knitted garment, while the caregiver’s gloved fingers handle it gently.\n\nThe baby returns to view lying peacefully in the incubator on the white bedding, still wearing the diaper and the red boxing-glove mitten, with the clear tube near the nose. Over the image, the red HUGGIES logo appears, with white text beneath it reading “Designed with NICU Nurses.” The small bottom disclaimer about the baby being AI-created for safety in the NICU remains visible as the final image holds on the resting infant.",
